 :NEW , :OLD variables :- 
 ===================

 => these two variables are called bind variables  and rowtype variables
 => the data affected by dmls are copied to :NEW, :OLD variables
 => the record user is trying to insert is copied to :NEW variable
 => the record user is trying to delete is copied to :OLD variable
 => the record user is trying to update is copied to both :NEW & :OLD variables 
 => these two variables are allowed only in row level triggers but not allowed in stmt level triggers 


    INSERT INTO emp VALUES(100,'A','clerk',---,sysdate,3000,200,20)  => :NEW
 
    DELETE FROM emp WHERE empno = 7844   =>  :OLD

    UPDATE emp SET sal = 5000 WHERE empno = 7369;    =>    :OLD
						    empno	sal
						    7369	4300

						   :NEW
						   empno	sal
						   7369	5000

